Sentencas: Ni-based alloy cermet anodes,Ni1-xCux (x = 0.0, 0.2, 0.5, and 1.0)/Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC), were prepared for use with syngas fuel in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells by in situ reduction of Ni1-xCuxO compounds.
Titulo: Electrochemical performances of Ni1-xCux/SDC cermet anodes for intermediate-temperature SOFCs using syngas fuel

Sentencas: The electrochemical performances of cells with the Ni1-xCux/SDC anodes were investigated at 700 and 600 degrees C, using humidified (3% H2O) syngas with H-2/CO = 3/2 as the fuel.
Titulo: Electrochemical performances of Ni1-xCux/SDC cermet anodes for intermediate-temperature SOFCs using syngas fuel

Sentencas: Cu doping of the Ni/SDC anode effectively suppressed carbon deposition on the anode.
Titulo: Electrochemical performances of Ni1-xCux/SDC cermet anodes for intermediate-temperature SOFCs using syngas fuel

Sentencas: However, the cell performance was deteriorated with increasing amounts of Cu.
Titulo: Electrochemical performances of Ni1-xCux/SDC cermet anodes for intermediate-temperature SOFCs using syngas fuel

Sentencas: The Ni0.8Cu0.2/SDC anode was found to be promising for use with syngas fuel.
Titulo: Electrochemical performances of Ni1-xCux/SDC cermet anodes for intermediate-temperature SOFCs using syngas fuel
